Responsibilities

  Conduct regular health checks on SCADA and PLC system
  Maintain SCADA system and work processes in line with CCoP requirements
  Liaise with authorities on cyber security matters including review alerts from authorities; respond to alerts from authorities; respond to cyber alerts or any other matters.
  Plan tasks to close out cyber related matters
  Conduct training/drill/pre-audit checks and assist in actual audit activities
  Review documents and policies relevant to cybersecurity to ensure compliance
  Co-ordinate statutory compliance projects with vendors
  Perform system patching and scanning periodically

Requirements

  Bachelor Degree in Engineering or Computer Sciences
  5 years of relevant experience
  Experienced with SCADA iFIX and PLC (Siemens)
  Familiar with Cybersecurity Act

EA Lic 04C3537